Confluence users who modify Confluence source have limited options for checking for source-code modifications, apart from a time-stamp check. Users may be running on modified source without realising it, and this creates problems for support and upgrades.

Each Confluence build should have properties file containing a hash of every class file. In Administration, there should be an option called 'Check Source For Changes' that verifies each class against the hash, and logged a list of modified classes either to the UI or the output log.

