ConfluenceActionSupport uses the Action classname as a key to lookup the display value in ConfluenceActionSupport.properties:
    public String getActionName(String fullClassName)
    {
        //fullClassName will be in the form: com.atlassian.confluence.admin.actions.DailyBackupAdminAction
        String key = fullClassName + ".action.name";
        return getText(key);
    }
And - ConfluenceActionSupport.properties:
com.atlassian.confluence.pages.actions.ViewPageAction.action.name=View

If the action classes are sub-classes then the ConfluenceActionSupport.properties entries needs duplicating:
com.atlassian.confluence.pages.actions.ViewPageAction.action.name=View
com.ptc.ssp.se.tools.confluence.actions.logging.LoggingViewPageAction.action.name=View

This is a problem when upgrading server releases.

A key field in the action class which could be inherited by the sub-class would resolve this problem.
This field could be accessed by the getActionName method in ConfluenceActionSupport.  Or stored by the action class in a look up table in ConfluenceActionSupport.java and retrieved by getActionName.

