Note: this is duplicate xwork package *names* and not *namespaces*. Namespaces are added together happily as long as the same action name isnt used in the same namespace.

My suggestion is to prefix package names with the plugin key so <package name="actions" extends="default" namespace="/acp"> would become <package name="com.adaptavist.pluginKey:actions" extends="default" namespace="/acp"> internally. This should have no runtime effect other than to change the internal referencing of the package.

In XWorkModuleDescriptor change:

    protected PackageConfig buildPackageContext(Element packageElement, Configuration configuration)
    {
        String name = TextUtils.noNull(packageElement.attributeValue("name"));

to

    protected PackageConfig buildPackageContext(Element packageElement, Configuration configuration)
    {
        String name = getPluginKey() +":"+ TextUtils.noNull(packageElement.attributeValue("name"));

This is untested and is patched against Confluence 2.3-DR1's source - however logically it should work and is worth a try. To test it - simply create two basic xwork plugins and have them share the same package name, but with different action names ... then modify until both action names are visible simultaniously.

